      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلنُّثَارِ مِنَ اَلسُّكَّرِ وَ اَللَّوْزِ وَ أَشْبَاهِهِ أَ يَحِلُّ أَكْلُهُ فَقَالَ \"يُكْرَهُ كُلُّ مَالٍ يُنْتَهَبُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3586 - It is narrated from Ali ibn Ja'far, from his brother Imam Musa ibn Jafar Al-Kadhim (as), who said:\n\"I asked him about scattered treats such as sugar, almonds, and similar items-whether it is permissible to eat them.\nImam (as) replied: 'It is disliked to consume anything that is seized unlawfully.'\""
        ]
      }
    },
